cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with joint embeddings between medical imaging modalities and associated radiology reports, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses unsupervised and supervised methods for learning representations, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal representation learning, which is a topic in cs.MM (Multimedia).
